The paper discusses the detection of advanced persistent threats (APTs) in computer systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of unsupervised anomaly detection algorithms, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG). The study involves analyzing large amounts of data, which could fall under the category of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of monitoring system-level activity, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
